
Get the comments from a PR in a reasonable format ($pr should be an integer):
url=repos/$(gh repo view --json nameWithOwner --jq .nameWithOwner)/pulls/${pr?}/comments
gh api "$url" --jq '.[] | {id, body}'


Reply to a comment:
url=repos/$(gh repo view --json nameWithOwner --jq .nameWithOwner)/pulls/${pr?}/comments
gh api "${url}" -f body="your reply" -F in_reply_to=${comment_id}


Reply to a top-level comment:
gh pr comment ${pr} --body "your reply"


Resolve a conversation:
        This requires the GraphQL API — there's no REST endpoint for it.
        First, find the thread IDs:

        gh api graphql -f query="
          {
            repository(owner: \"{$owner?}\", name: \"${repo?}\") {
              pullRequest(number: ${pr?}) {
                reviewThreads(first: 100) {
                  nodes {
                    id
                    isResolved
                    comments(first: 1) {
                      nodes { body }
                    }
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          }'

        Then resolve a thread by its node ID:

        gh api graphql -f query="
          mutation {
            resolveReviewThread(input: {threadId: \"${thread_id?}\"}) {
              thread { isResolved }
            }
          }"
